  <h2 id="introheader" style="font-size: 1.2em; padding-bottom: 15px;">Cognitive Control</h2>
  <p id="intro">Research in our lab focuses on the neurobiological mechanisms underlying cognitive control. Cognitive control is the ability to guide attention, thought and action in accord with goals or intentions. One of the fundamental mysteries of neuroscience is how this capacity for coordinated, purposeful behavior arises from the distributed activity of many billions of neurons in the brain. To learn more, click on one of the topics below.</p>

